VALUES
(44, 16, 30, 42, 3, 10, 10, NULL, 'Inquiry About Salvation', 'Both passages emphasize a question about what actions are necessary for salvation or righteousness. The inquiry in Acts reflects a direct concern for salvation, while the question in Luke seeks guidance on moral conduct.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 16, 30, 44, 14, 15, 15, 'what must I do to be saved', 'Call to Salvation and God', 'Both passages emphasize a call to turn to the living God for salvation. The question of what must be done to be saved in Acts 16:30 connects with the call to turn from vanities to the living God in Acts 14:15.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 16, 30, 59, 2, 13, 13, 'what must I do to be saved?', 'Salvation and Mercy Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of salvation and mercy. The question of what must be done to be saved in Acts 16:30 relates to the idea in James 2:13 that mercy is essential in the judgment process.', 'theme', 0.321, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 16, 31, 43, 1, 12, 12, 'Believe on the Lord Jesus Christ', 'Salvation through Belief', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of belief in Jesus for salvation. Acts 16:31 states that belief leads to salvation for oneself and one''s household, while John 1:12 highlights that receiving and believing in Jesus grants the power to become God''s children.', 'theme', 0.566, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 16, 31, 43, 3, 36, 36, 'Believe on the Lord Jesus Christ', 'Salvation through Belief', 'This connection highlights the theme of belief as essential for salvation. Both passages emphasize that belief in Jesus leads to everlasting life and salvation for oneself and one''s household.', 'theme', 0.5589999999999999, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 16, 31, 44, 2, 38, 39, 'thou shalt be saved, and thy house', 'Salvation and Promise Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of salvation and the promise of God extending to families. Acts 16:31 speaks of salvation for the household, while Acts 2:39 mentions the promise being for children and those afar off.', 'theme', 0.5449999999999999, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 16, 31, 45, 10, 9, 10, 'Believe on the Lord Jesus Christ', 'Salvation Through Belief and Confession', 'This connection highlights the theme of salvation through belief in Jesus Christ. Both passages emphasize the necessity of faith and confession for salvation.', 'theme', 0.524, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 16, 31, 44, 11, 13, 14, 'thy house', 'Salvation for Households', 'Both passages emphasize the promise of salvation extending to one''s household. Acts 16:31 states that belief in Jesus leads to salvation for ''thy house,'' while Acts 11:14 mentions words that will bring salvation to ''all thy house.''', 'theme', 0.46799999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 16, 31, 41, 16, 16, 16, 'Believe on the Lord Jesus Christ', 'Salvation Through Belief', 'Both passages emphasize the necessity of belief for salvation. Acts 16:31 states, ''Believe on the Lord Jesus Christ,'' while Mark 16:16 mentions, ''He that believeth... shall be saved.''', 'theme', 0.43299999999999994, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 16, 31, 48, 3, 26, 26, 'Believe on the Lord Jesus Christ', 'Faith and Salvation Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of salvation through faith in Christ. Both passages emphasize the importance of belief in Jesus for becoming children of God.', 'theme', 0.426, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 16, 32, 45, 1, 16, 16, 'the word of the Lord', 'Connection of Salvation and Belief', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of belief in the gospel for salvation. Acts 16:32 mentions sharing the word of the Lord, which aligns with Romans 1:16''s focus on the gospel''s power to save those who believe.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 16, 32, 51, 1, 27, 28, 'the word of the Lord', 'Preaching and Teaching Connection', 'This connection highlights the act of preaching the word of the Lord in both passages. In Acts, the word is shared with the jailer and his household, while in Colossians, the preaching aims to present every man perfect in Christ.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 16, 32, 52, 2, 8, 8, 'the word of the Lord', 'Affectionate Sharing of the Gospel', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of sharing the gospel with deep personal connection. Acts 16:32 highlights the imparting of the word of the Lord, while 1 Thessalonians 2:8 expresses a willingness to share not only the gospel but also their own souls.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 16, 32, 54, 1, 13, 16, NULL, 'Connection of Mercy and Salvation', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of mercy and salvation. In Acts, the word of the Lord is shared, leading to belief, while in 1 Timothy, the author reflects on receiving mercy despite past sins, highlighting the transformative power of faith in Christ.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 16, 32, 41, 16, 15, 15, 'the word of the Lord', 'Preaching the Gospel', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of sharing the word of the Lord. Acts 16:32 reflects the fulfillment of the command in Mark 16:15 to preach the gospel to all.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 16, 32, 44, 10, 33, 43, 'the word of the Lord', 'Preaching the Word of God', 'Both passages emphasize the act of sharing the word of the Lord with others. In Acts 16:32, the word is spoken to the jailer and his household, while in Acts 10:33-43, Peter addresses a gathering to share God''s message.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 16, 32, 49, 3, 8, 8, 'the word of the Lord', 'Preaching to the Gentiles', 'This connection highlights the act of preaching the word of the Lord to others, as seen in both passages. Acts 16:32 mentions speaking the word to a household, while Ephesians 3:8 emphasizes preaching among the Gentiles.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 16, 33, 46, 1, 16, 16, 'baptized, he and all his', 'Baptism of Households', 'Both passages emphasize the baptism of entire households, highlighting the communal aspect of faith. Acts 16:33 mentions the baptism of the jailer''s household, while 1 Corinthians 1:16 refers to the baptism of Stephanas'' household.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 16, 33, 44, 16, 15, 15, 'baptized, he and all his', 'Baptism and Household Salvation', 'Both passages emphasize the act of baptism occurring with the entire household. This connection highlights the communal aspect of faith and salvation in early Christian practice.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 16, 33, 42, 10, 33, 34, 'washed their stripes', 'Compassion and Healing Connection', 'This connection highlights the themes of compassion and healing in both passages. In Acts, the jailer cares for Paul and Silas by washing their wounds, while in Luke, the Samaritan shows compassion by binding up the wounded man''s wounds.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 16, 33, 44, 16, 25, 25, NULL, 'Prayer and Immediate Response', 'Both passages emphasize the immediacy of response to faith. In Acts 16:25, Paul and Silas''s prayers lead to a transformative event, culminating in the baptism mentioned in Acts 16:33.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 16, 33, 20, 16, 7, 7, 'washed their stripes', 'Peace Through Righteous Actions', 'This connection highlights how acts of kindness, such as washing the stripes of the imprisoned, can lead to peace and reconciliation, as seen in both passages. The act of baptism following the washing signifies a transformation that aligns with pleasing the Lord.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 16, 33, 23, 11, 6, 9, NULL, 'Transformation and Restoration', 'This connection highlights the theme of transformation and restoration found in both passages. In Acts, the immediate washing and baptism signify a new beginning, while Isaiah envisions a future where natural enemies coexist peacefully, symbolizing restoration and harmony.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 16, 33, 40, 25, 35, 40, 'washed their stripes', 'Acts and Matthew''s Compassion Theme', 'This connection highlights the theme of compassion and care for those in need. In Acts, the jailer cares for Paul and Silas by washing their stripes, while in Matthew, Jesus emphasizes the importance of caring for the least among us.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 16, 34, 45, 15, 13, 13, 'rejoiced, believing in God', 'Connection of Joy and Belief', 'Both passages emphasize the themes of joy and belief in God. In Acts, the jailer rejoices after believing, while Romans speaks of being filled with joy and peace in believing.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 16, 34, 44, 2, 46, 46, 'rejoiced, believing in God', 'Joyful Fellowship in Belief', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of joy and communal meals among believers. In Acts 16:34, the jailer rejoices with his household after believing in God, while Acts 2:46 describes the early church sharing meals with gladness.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 16, 34, 45, 5, 11, 11, 'rejoiced, believing in God', 'Joy in God and Belief', 'This connection highlights the theme of rejoicing in God. Both passages emphasize joy as a response to faith and belief in God.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 16, 34, 57, 1, 7, 7, 'rejoiced, believing in God', 'Joy and Refreshment in Faith', 'This connection highlights the theme of joy found in both passages. In Acts, the jailer rejoices after believing in God, while in Philemon, joy is expressed through the love that refreshes the saints.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 16, 34, 23, 12, 1, 3, 'rejoiced, believing in God', 'Joy and Salvation Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of joy in salvation. In Acts 16:34, the jailer rejoices after believing in God, while Isaiah 12:3 speaks of drawing joy from the wells of salvation.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
